originContent: | | Plug-and-play background program that puts your current Destiny 2 activity in your Discord status. Modern, no flaky screenshots and tiny in size. |
translatedContent: | | Plug-and-play background program that puts your current Destiny 2 activity in your Discord status. Modern, no flaky screenshots and tiny in size. |

originContent: If you want to contribute, awesome! For new features, please ask first on the Discord server or make an issue with what you want to make. If you want to fix a bug, just create a PR. Asking is still recommended however, in case "it's not a bug, it's a feature."
translatedContent: If you want to contribute, awesome! For new features, please ask first on the Discord server or make an issue with what you want to make. If you want to fix a bug, just create a PR. Asking is still recommended however, in case "it's not a bug, it's a feature."

originContent: - (client) For windows: have git bash. You can also run the commands in the build script manually but I use the bash script :)
translatedContent: - (client) For windows: have git bash. You can also run the commands in the build script manually but I use the bash script :)

originContent: - (web) Have a recent version of Node.js and npm.
translatedContent: - (web) Have a recent version of Node.js and npm.

originContent: - Duplicate the `config.go.example` to `config.go` and fill in the values. For redirect uri, you can use `https://richdestiny.app/login` -- also on the Bungie.net developer portal. It's just a redirect to the localhost redirect.
translatedContent: - Duplicate the `config.go.example` to `config.go` and fill in the values. For redirect uri, you can use `https://richdestiny.app/login` -- also on the Bungie.net developer portal. It's just a redirect to the localhost redirect.

originContent: - You can use `./build vX.Y.Z` with a valid semver version number, but for development purposes use dev. It automatically disables updates and possibly other things in the future.
translatedContent: - You can use `./build vX.Y.Z` with a valid semver version number, but for development purposes use dev. It automatically disables updates and possibly other things in the future.

originContent: - `npm run start` for a local development server or `npm run build` for a production build.
translatedContent: - `npm run start` for a local development server or `npm run build` for a production build.
